    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="152"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Dun</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 9, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The following telegram has been received from Allen, dated Seoul, October 9:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Yesterday morning King’s father, with the assistance of Japanese,
                            forcibly entered into royal palace. Two officers killed in attempting to
                            save Her Majesty. Queen and three ladies murdered. Murderers were
                            Japanese in civilian dress. King’s father is making a great many changes
                            in the administration. The people are quiet. Royal palace in charge of
                            Japanese troops.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dun.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
